Epic in praise of Kim Il Sung
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 5 (KCNA) -- Rodong Sinmun yesterday carried an epic "May song of the great eternal life last forever" written by Kim Man Yong on the occasion of the 5th anniversary of the President Kim Il Sung's passing away.
   Kim Il Sung Prize winner Kim Man Yong dedicated long epics to the first and third anniversaries of President Kim Il Sung's passing away.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   In the epic, he said:  President Kim Il Sung is immortal along with the history of the country which is prospering under the guidance of the great leader Kim Jong Il.
   It is Kim Jong Il identical with Kim Il Sung, who filled an aching void in the hearts of the people left by the passing away of the President. He is the dear father who offered the same love and affection to the people in the past 5 years as the President did.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The last 5 years is a period during which the Korean people have grasped the great truth taught by the President that Marshal Kim Jong Il is the destinies of the people, the country and the revolution.
   The President and the Marshal were always together on the road of serving the people and the Marshal further intensified the struggle to accomplish the cause of revolution pioneered by the President in the last 5 years after his passing away.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   It is our Marshal who paved the way for the building of a powerful nation, breaking through manifold difficulties and trials with his revolutionary leadership art of giving priority to military affairs.
   The President is immortal thanks to the Marshal who is carrying on the revolution and the construction in accordance with the idea and will of the President, upholding him as the eternal President of the republic, and the people have become one big family of the President under the leadership of the Marshal who is identical with the President.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   In the past five years. Korea has grown strong in ideology, faith, will and national power and Kim Il Sung is immortal forever under the leadership of Kim Jong Il who has proved himself to be a great communist leader to the world.

Library on Kim Il Sung's feats off press
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 5 (KCNA) -- Volume 12 "Realization of Single-Hearted Unity of Whole Society" and volume 13 "Building of Independent Socialist National Economy", serials of a library "Undying Revolutionary Feats of the Great Leader Comrade Kim Il Sung", were published by the Worker's Party of Korea Publishing House on the occasion of the 5th anniversary of the passing away of President Kim Il Sung.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The volume 12 has three parts and 10 chapters.
The part 1 deals with the ideological and theoretical achievements scored by the President by advancing the idea and theory on the single-hearted unity for the first time in history on the basis of the Juche idea and systematizing them in an integral way as well as the greatness of the achievements.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The part 2 gives an all-round exposition of the greatness and sagacity of the leadership of the President, who considered it as a fundamental issue of the revolution to creditably train the driving forces of the revolution and enhance their role in the whole course of the Korean revolution from  the very day he set on the road of revolution in his early years under the banner of "down-with-imperialism" and victoriously led the struggle to materialize it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
The part 3 deals with the single-hearted unity of the leader, the party and the masses  achieved by the President and with the tremendous significance it carries in the development of the Korean revolution and in the accomplishment of the human cause of independence.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The volume 13 has three parts and seven chapters.
   The parts 1 and 2 give an explanation of the  clear-sighted leadership of the President, who advanced the theory on building  an independent socialist national economy and energetically led the struggle  for its materialization.
   The part 3 deals with the greatness of the revolutionary feats the President performed by attaining the historic cause of building the independent socialist national economy and with its enduring significance.

Monumental creations representative of loyalty and filial piety
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;   Pyongyang, July 5 (KCNA) -- Many monumental creations were built in Korea in the last 5 years.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Chongryu Bridge (the second stage), Kumnung Tunnel no.2, September 9 Street, April 25 Hotel and many other monumental creations have been built in Pyongyang.  The Anbyon Youth Power Station and minor power stations have made their appearance in different parts of the country.  The Pyongyang-Hyangsan Tourist Highway has been built and Mt. Chilbo, Mt. Kuwol, Mt. Jongbang and other scenic spots have turned into cultural and rest places for the people.  And the appearance of Kangwon Province has changed beyond recognition with the completion of vast nature-remaking projects, the first artificial satellite "Kwangmyongsong 1" was successfully launched and the Korean method of iron production was invented.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The credit for all this goes to the loyalty and filial piety and wise leadership of General Secretary Kim Jong Il who has made unremitting efforts to creditably realise the lifetime intention of the President Kim Il Sung.
   Kim Jong Il found his great happiness in realising intentions and plans of the President one by one, always thinking of him in the last 5 years.
   With the single-hearted desire to realize the behest of the President, he made historic initiatives, held meetings of activists in different sectors for their materialization and gave on-the-spot guidance to many units in this period.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   People of the world are deeply moved by the fact that Kim Jong Il  wrought this historic miracle by wisely leading the people to build many monumental edifices under the extremely unfavorable conditions where the country was put under the tense situation in which a war may break out any time, the imperialists persisted in their  vicious moves to isolate and stifle  the DPRK and the various fields of the national economy  faced difficulties and trials due to years of natural disasters. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The Korean people are now making all efforts to erect more monumental creations of eternal value in the era of the workers' party while building a powerful nation under the leadership of General Secretary Kim Jong Il.

Kim Il Sung's immortal poem carved
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;   Pyongyang, July 5 (KCNA) -- The President Kim Il Sung's immortal poem "an Autumnal Day in Mt. Myohyang" was carved on a natural rock at Mt. Myohyang with the approach of the 5th anniversary of his passing away.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The title of the poem carved in over 500 square metres is 1.5 metres high, 1.3 metres wide and 0.15 metre deep.  Each letter of the poem is 0.9 metre high, 0.7 metre wide and 0.09 metre deep. 
   The President visited Mt. Myohyang, a famous mountain in the northwestern part of Korea, on October 15, Juche 68 (1979), 20 years ago.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   At the international friendship exhibition situated there,  the President, in deep thought, saw precious gifts sent by many foreign party, state and government leaders, prominent political and public figures and  individual persons representing their reverence for him,  and said that these gifts are a pride and honor of the nation. 
   The President, who was commanding a bird's-eye view of the scenery of Mt. Myohyang in the balcony of the exhibition, recited his immortal poem "an autumnal day in Mt. Myohyang" in a low voice.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The poem vividly represented the past, present and future of the Korean nation and concentrically manifested the Korean nation-first spirit reflected in the beautiful scenery of the country  and his ardent love of the country. 
   Kim Ki Nam, secretary of the Central Committee of the Worker's Party of Korea, was present at the unveiling ceremony held on July 4.

Korean people's struggle supported
 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;   Pyongyang, July 5 (KCNA) -- Solidarity rallies were held in various countries including Cuba, Peru, Nepal, Romania, Tajikistan, Poland, the Czech Republic and France in the month of international solidarity with the Korean people (June 25-July 27.)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The speakers said at the rallies that the U.S. imperialists unleashed a war of aggression against the Democratic People's Republic of Korea in the 1950s but the Korean people under the wise leadership of the President Kim Il Sung defeated the U.S. imperialists and achieved a brilliant victory in the Fatherland Liberation War.
   They went on:   Nearly 50 years have passed since the end of the war but the Korean people's desire for reunification has not yet been realized. The outside interference in Korea and the occupation of South Korea by the U.S. troops should be terminated for the independent and peaceful reunification of Korea.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The Korean People's Army has grown to be an invincible army with powerful defensive and modern offensive means  thanks to the great Marshal Kim Jong Il's revolutionary leadership art of giving priority to military affairs. The U.S. imperialists and the South Korean authorities will be defeated by the invincible might of the Korean people and revolutionary armed forces.
   They extended firm solidarity to the Korean people's struggle to reunify the country independently and peacefully. They said they will make all their efforts to prevent the danger of war and ensure peace in the Korean peninsula.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Messages of solidarity to General Secretary Kim Jong Il were adopted at the rallies in Nepal, Poland and the Czech Republic and a letter in Peru.

Tire production on steady increase
 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;   Pyongyang, July 5 (KCNA) -- The Amnokgang Tire Plant situated in the northwestern part of Korea is bringing about a great upsurge in production.
The plant has over fulfilled its monthly production target for five months this year.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The plant is carrying out its daily assignments at 120-140 percent this month.
   When General Secretary Kim Jong Il visited the plant in the middle of June, he was very satisfied with production process in full-capacity operation.   Last year the plant faced the biggest difficulties in 30 odd years after its commissioning because of shortage of imported materials, electric power and raw materials caused by the persistent economic blockade of the imperialists and  continued natural disasters.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Kim Jong Il visited the plant last October and acquainted himself with its performance. He taught its officials to take an  optimistic view of the reality and boldly press ahead with the work on the principle of self-reliance  by making the best use of its great production potential. He indicated concrete ways of enterprise management such as attaching importance to science and effecting technological innovation to tap long-term potential and maintaining the socialist principle and applying economic method well to ensure actual profits.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The workers, encouraged by this, made all efforts to keep all equipment in full-capacity operation by tapping potential with high revolutionary enthusiasm.
   They have introduced into production the electric-guided heating system, robotized production process and various technical innovation proposals so as to keep production of tire going on a high level.
   The workers of the plant are registering signal successes in their drive to increase tire production.
